I'm a Sea Hawk fan all of the way - but, I think that they have been lucky and just good enough to eak out the win in a couple of games that they really shouldn't have won this ason. Opponent's missed last second field goals come to mind.



For me, its awesome that they even made the playoffs. I think that Pete should be named coach of the year for the job that he and his staff have done considering the injuries and inexperienced players with which they started the season. Team members have grown their skills and matured as the season progressed.



Kudos to Pete and his staff and to the members of the team. Of course, the key guy this year as in the past years is Russel. He is the MVP hands down this season in my opinion. Way to go, guys - I think that you have way over achieved this season. Very entertaining - I'm happy for you all.
